No short answers :) Ever tried that your new templatetag library isn't discovered? That's because runserver doesn't see **new files**. That's the same with hooks that live in files that didn't exist pre-runserver, unless it's a file that belongs to a new app that you've just added to INSTALLED_APPS and it gets loaded for the very first time.

@yashu-seth Why are you making the `ContinuousFactor` to work only on single variables. No matter how the parent  child relation is (as you have mentioned in the blog post), it's pdf can be represented by a single function. So, this is my idea of `ContinuousFactor`:
```python
ContinuousFactor
    def __init__(var, pdf):
        "Initialize the values"
    def discretize(method):
        "Return maybe a Factor instance"
    def sum/divide/product(other factor):
        "returns a function (pdf)"
    def marginalize(var):
        "integrate over one axis and return the function (or replace self.pdf if inplace=True)"
    def reduce(var):
        "Return a new function representing the new pdf"
    def assignment(x1, [x2, x3,. ..]):
        "Return an single float value"
```
And then the special cases of say LinearGaussianCPD should inherit this ContinuousFactor class and in the special cases we should be able to compute these methods more efficiently. So, we can overload them with the efficient implementation.

