I'm still confused by the issue. Are there any special rules for the random seed on smt2 files? Or does it have a fixed seed different to the C API default?

Changing the random seed does indeed change the time taken to solve, however the problem always solves within a second on my local machine z3 binary. I can execute it repeatedly and it never takes particularly long.

